                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Creating Stories and Dealing with the Sequence of execution&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Create User Stories (Work) and associate them to the Product Backlog Record that you created.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For each story, a sequence will be defined automatically. This sequence will be used to define the priority for the funcionalities desired.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;You can reorder the user Stories as you wish. When you change the number in the &amp;ldquo;Sequence&amp;rdquo; field, remember to refresh the List View to see the result. All other Stories will be reorganized as well.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Creating a Sprint and Associating Stories to it&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now you can create your first Sprint. When you do it, set the Start and End Dates (as the information you provided when creating the Project in &amp;ldquo;Sprint Duration&amp;rdquo;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Now you can associate Stories to your sprint. Keep in mind that only Stories that are estimated (Estimated Points field) can be included to a sprint.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Start your Sprint&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When you create a Sprint, the Sprint Status is set to Planned. To start a Sprint, change the Sprint Status to &amp;ldquo;In Progress&amp;rdquo;. When you do it, you&amp;rsquo;ll be able to see the Sprint Burndown chart in the Sprint record page. All the metrics will be calculed base in the Sprint Duration x Estimated Points.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;You can only have one Sprint in progress at a time (for the same Project). You can create how many sprints that you wish in the &amp;ldquo;Planned&amp;rdquo; status. Do it so you can have a roadmap of what should go out on the next Sprints.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;You are able to move the user Stories from Sprint or back to the Product Backlog. Sprint Metrics and Sprint Burndown will be automatically updated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Moving Stories and Sequence Behavior&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When you move one story from the Product Backlog to a Sprint, this story will enter as the last item in the sequence. The same happens when you move a Story between sprints.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When you remove a story from a Sprint back to the Product Backlog, it will be the set as the first item of the sequence of the Product Backlog.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;Important: Sprint Dates are not supposed to the change!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A Sprint have start and end dates, and they should not be changed. If there&amp;rsquo;s no time to finish one or more Stories in a sprint, you should move them to the next Sprint.&lt;/p&gt;</value>
